reviews.review_text:
Hooo boy I think Bobby is actually carrying most of the vocal duties for this one, although Mickey is audible at the beginning.  As for Phil's "lead guitar", it's completely absent, as far as I can hear.

Rough.
Nice Well I can certainly listen Phil's bass and there's some good if not great rendition there. Looks like rain got me in pretty good.

- One thing of which to be aware for the purposes of this review is that I find the first set so boring in content that I couldn't really be bothered to listen to much of its form, but what little I did sounded hum-drum as well. The 2nd set picks up quite a bit, but despite some awesome moments I still don't consider it quite a keeper.
Delightful! First Set I am thoroughly enjoying this show. Jerry's guitar work is delicate, intricate, and intuitive...the band is having a ball and I've just listened to the first set...
